graph.tree.spqr

Class SPQRTree<V extends Vertex,E extends Edge<V>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • graph.elements.Graph<SPQRTreeNode<V,TreeEdgeWithContent<V,E>>,Edge<SPQRTreeNode<V,TreeEdgeWithContent<V,E>>>>
      • graph.tree.spqr.AbstractTree<V,E>
        • graph.tree.spqr.SPQRTree<V,E>

  • public class SPQRTree<V extends Vertex,E extends Edge<V>>
extends AbstractTree<V,E>
    SPQR-trees implicitly represent all embeddings of a graph The triconnected components of a biconnected graph are a system of smaller graphs that describe all of the 2-vertex cuts in the graph. An SPQR tree is used to represent the triconnected components of a graph.
